Checks
======
- tcp/perfs
    . ssh
    . ntp
    . ldap
    . smtp
    . ftp
    . http
    . https
    . pop
    . nntp
    . imap
    . telnet
 - ssl validity. To check TCP service using SSL, use checkTCP --with-ssl

 - udp/perfs
    . dhcp
    . dns
    . smb

- snmp
    . cpu/ram
    . ifperfs
    . routing protocols

- wmi
    . cpu/ram
    . processes/services?
    . check updates (windows updates) (nograph)

- (ssh? wmi? other?)
    . check apt (nograph)
    . check yum (nograph)


API
===
- Native Java API (allow use of nchecks from other languages),
- Erlang API as module,
- Offer "opaque" state data to checks ,
- Include snmpman,
- Include an "helper" API. Will allow to run a function
  to get (for example):
    . ifIndexes to choose from,
    . discover/autofill configuration flags (for example what alg for
      monitoring CPU, RAM, ect wich is different for Cisco/hP/others/?).
- Allow nograph xml def


Packaging
=========
- Make javapackager (single executable)

